<title>USA: Rational-Pure Atria proxy effective.</title>
<headline>Rational-Pure Atria proxy effective.</headline>
<dateline>SANTA CLARA, Calif. 1997-06-25</dateline>
<text>
<p>Rational Software Corp said Wednesday the Securities and Exchange Commission has declared effective the joint proxy statement for the proposed $839 million merger of Rational and Pure Atria Corp.</p>
<p>Rational said proxy statements will be mailed to stockholders shortly. The companies' special meetings for stockholders are scheduled for July 30.</p>
<p>The merger must gain stockholder approval and antitrust clearance, the company said.</p>
<p>Both companies write development tools, a type of software that helps programmers write other software.</p>
